Type: Package
Package: RGISTools
Title: Tools for Downloading and Processing Time-Series of Satellite Images
Version: 0.9.2
Author: U PÃ©rez - Goya [aut, cre] <unai.perez@unavarra.es>,
        A F Militino [aut] <militino@unavarra.es>,
        M D Ugarte [aut] <lola@unavarra.es>,
        M Montesino - SanMartin [aut] <manuel.montesino@unavarra.es>
Maintainer: U Perez - Goya <unai.perez@unavarra.es>
Description: Downloading and filling time series of satellite images in a region of interest. RGISTools functions allow a unified access to multispectral images from the Landsat, MODIS and Sentinel repositories. RGISTools  also offers capabilities for processing satellite images, including tile mosaicking, cropping and extracting the variables of interest.   Finally, the package implements  the genFillingIMA and genSmoothingIMA functions for gap-filling time-series of images.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0), raster, gdalUtils
Imports: sp, Rdpack, XML, xml2, utils, fields, magick, urltools, rjson, rvest, tools,  methods, curl 
